goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the frequency of flight delays and the range of delay times.

goals.question: What is the average delay time for flights?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the median and outliers of the delay times, giving us a better understanding of the typical delay time.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight distances?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the frequency of flight distances and the range of distance traveled.

goals.question: Which airports have the most delays?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of delay by origin airport
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the airports with the highest number of delays, which could be useful for airlines and passengers to avoid.

goals.question: What is the relationship between flight distance and delay time?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of distance vs delay
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a correlation between flight distance and delay time, which could be useful for airlines to optimize their flight schedules.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue', bins=30)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight delays?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Delay (minutes)")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title("What is the average delay time for flights?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    delay_by_origin = data.groupby('origin')['delay'].sum().reset_index()
    delay_by_origin = delay_by_origin.sort_values('delay', ascending=False)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='origin', y='delay', data=delay_by_origin)
    plt.title('Which airports have the most delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Origin Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Total Delay (minutes)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='distance', y='delay', hue='origin', palette='viridis', legend='full')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between flight distance and delay time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.legend(title='Origin Airport', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
